2021
01:58:45,347 --> 01:58:47,597
Let's just wrap it up.

2022
01:58:47,598 --> 01:58:50,391
- Come in and we'll tell Mom.
- I don't want to see her.

2023
01:58:50,392 --> 01:58:52,225
- Come on.
- I don't want to see her.

2024
01:58:52,226 --> 01:58:54,770
Don't bother me, will ya?

2025
01:58:54,771 --> 01:58:57,396
Dad, what do you mean?
You don't want to see her?

2026
01:58:57,397 --> 01:59:01,026
Pop, you don't want them
calling you yellow, do you?

2027
01:59:01,109 --> 01:59:05,235
Dad, it's not your fault.
It's me. I'm a bum.

2028
01:59:05,320 --> 01:59:07,796
Now, come on inside.

2029
01:59:08,531 --> 01:59:11,883
Dad, did you hear what I said to you?

2030
01:59:18,371 --> 01:59:20,640
Did you plant, dear?

2031
01:59:22,083 --> 01:59:24,685
All right, Mom.

2032
01:59:25,835 --> 01:59:29,089
We had it out.
I'm going and I'm not writing anymore.

2033
01:59:29,172 --> 01:59:31,131
I think it's best, Willy.

2034
01:59:31,132 --> 01:59:34,218
There's no use drawing it out.
You two will never get along.

2035
01:59:34,300 --> 01:59:37,261
If people ask where I am,
what I'm doing, you don't know or care.

2036
01:59:37,345 --> 01:59:41,473
That way it'll be off your mind
and you can start brightening up again.

2037
01:59:41,555 --> 01:59:44,116
All right?

2038
01:59:49,853 --> 01:59:52,664
That... That clears it, then, huh?

2039
02:00:08,660 --> 02:00:12,704
- You gonna wish me luck, scout?
- Shake his hand, Willy.

2040
02:00:12,788 --> 02:00:15,038
What do you say?

2041
02:00:15,039 --> 02:00:18,459
There's no necessity to mention...
He put his arm...!

2042
02:00:18,542 --> 02:00:22,254
Dad, you're never gonna see what I am,
so what's the use of arguing?

2043
02:00:22,338 --> 02:00:25,799
If I strike oil I'll send you a cheque.
Meantime, forget I'm alive.

2044
02:00:25,881 --> 02:00:27,882
Spite, see?

2045
02:00:27,883 --> 02:00:31,192
- Shake hands, Dad.
- Not my hand.

2046
02:00:35,848 --> 02:00:37,907
Dad?

2047
02:00:38,307 --> 02:00:42,304
- I was hoping not to go this way.
- This is the way you're going. Bye.

2048
02:00:46,088 --> 02:00:49,959
May you rot in hell
if you leave this house!

2049
02:00:50,044 --> 02:00:52,692
Exactly what is it
that you want from me?

2050
02:00:52,693 --> 02:00:56,562
I want you to know on the train,
in the mountains, in the valleys,

2051
02:00:56,647 --> 02:01:00,181
wherever you go,
that you cut down your life for spite!

2052
02:01:00,264 --> 02:01:03,435
- No, no!
- Spite!

2053
02:01:08,340 --> 02:01:12,421
When you are rotting somewhere
beside a railroad track, remember.

2054
02:01:12,505 --> 02:01:15,363
- Don't you blame it on me.
- I'm not blaming you.

2055
02:01:15,364 --> 02:01:17,931
I'm not taking the rap for this, hear?

2056
02:01:17,932 --> 02:01:21,043
- That's what I'm telling you.
- You're putting a knife in me.

2057
02:01:21,127 --> 02:01:23,903
Don't think I don't know
what you're doing.

2058
02:01:23,904 --> 02:01:26,637
All right, phoney.
Leave it there. Don't move it.

2059
02:01:26,638 --> 02:01:28,867
- What is that?
- You know damn well.

2060
02:01:28,868 --> 02:01:31,222
- I never saw that.
- You saw it, all right.

2061
02:01:31,223 --> 02:01:35,051
Mice didn't bring it into the cellar.
Is that supposed to make you a hero?

2062
02:01:35,135 --> 02:01:38,626
That supposed to make me sorry for you?
There will be no pity for you.

2063
02:01:38,710 --> 02:01:40,727
- Hear that? No pity.
- Hear the spite?

2064
02:01:40,728 --> 02:01:43,336
You're gonna get the truth,
what you are, what I am.

2065
02:01:43,337 --> 02:01:45,060
- Spite!
- Cut it out!

2066
02:01:45,061 --> 02:01:48,048
The man don't know who we are.
The man is gonna know.

2067
02:01:48,932 --> 02:01:51,876
We never told the truth
for ten minutes in this house.

2068
02:01:51,961 --> 02:01:54,861
- We always told truth.
- Are you the assistant buyer?

2069
02:01:54,862 --> 02:01:57,594
You're one of
the two assistants to the assistant.

2070
02:01:57,595 --> 02:02:00,288
- I'm practically...
- You are practically full of it.

2071
02:01:59,789 --> 02:02:02,102
- We all are. I'm through with it.
- Yeah.

2072
02:02:02,103 --> 02:02:05,063
- Hear this, Willy. This is me.
- I know you.

2073
02:02:05,299 --> 02:02:08,200
Do you know why I had no
address for three months?

2074
02:02:08,201 --> 02:02:10,933
I stole a suit in Kansas City
and I was in gaol.

2075
02:02:10,934 --> 02:02:14,301
- I suppose it's my fault.
- Stop crying, I'm through with it!

2076
02:02:14,385 --> 02:02:17,539
I stole myself
out of every good job since high school.

2077
02:02:17,623 --> 02:02:19,052
Whose fault is that?

2078
02:02:19,053 --> 02:02:22,419
I could never get anywhere
'cause you blew me so full of hot air

2079
02:02:22,545 --> 02:02:25,404
that I could never stand
taking orders from anybody.

2080
02:02:25,405 --> 02:02:27,718
- I hear that.
- Stop it!

2081
02:02:27,719 --> 02:02:30,579
I had to be boss big shot
in two weeks and I'm through.

2082
02:02:30,663 --> 02:02:33,102
- Then hang yourself for spite!
- No! No!

2083
02:02:33,103 --> 02:02:36,930
No, nobody is hanging himself, Willy.

2084
02:02:40,085 --> 02:02:44,670
I ran down 11 flights with a pen
in my hand today.

2085
02:02:44,754 --> 02:02:47,109
And suddenly I stopped.
Do you hear me?

2086
02:02:47,110 --> 02:02:50,474
In the middle of that office building...
Do you hear this?

2087
02:02:50,559 --> 02:02:52,704
I stopped...

2088
02:02:52,705 --> 02:02:56,784
...in the middle of the building
and I saw the sky!

2089
02:02:56,868 --> 02:03:02,800
And I... I... I saw the things
that I love in this world.

2090
02:03:02,926 --> 02:03:06,400
The work and the food

2091
02:03:06,586 --> 02:03:09,446
and the time to sit and smoke.

2092
02:03:09,530 --> 02:03:13,904
I looked at that pen in my hand and
I said, "What am I grabbing this for?

2093
02:03:13,988 --> 02:03:16,721
Why am I trying to become
what I don't want to be?

2094
02:03:16,722 --> 02:03:18,404
What am I doing in an office?

2095
02:03:18,405 --> 02:03:21,561
Making a contemptuous begging
fool of myself,

2096
02:03:21,644 --> 02:03:24,420
when all that I want
is out there waiting for me?"

2097
02:03:24,421 --> 02:03:27,785
The minute I say it, I know who I am.
Why can't I say that, Willy?

2098
02:03:27,869 --> 02:03:29,886
The door to your life is wide open!

2099
02:03:29,887 --> 02:03:32,410
Pop, I am a dime a dozen and so are you.

2100
02:03:32,411 --> 02:03:35,061
I am not a dime a dozen!

2101
02:03:35,062 --> 02:03:38,048
I am Willy Loman and you are Biff Loman!

2102
02:03:38,133 --> 02:03:41,968
I am not the leader of men, Willy!
And neither are you!

2103
02:03:42,171 --> 02:03:45,662
You were never anything
but a hard-working drummer

2104
02:03:45,788 --> 02:03:48,647
who landed in the ashcan
like all the rest of them.

2105
02:03:48,648 --> 02:03:51,298
I am one dollar an hour, Willy!

2106
02:03:51,299 --> 02:03:55,042
I am not bringing home
any prizes anymore,

2107
02:03:55,126 --> 02:03:57,312
and you're gonna stop waiting for me!

2108
02:03:57,313 --> 02:04:01,184
- You vengeful, spiteful mutt!
- Yeah, Pop!

2109
02:04:01,267 --> 02:04:04,254
Pop, I'm nothing.

2110
02:04:04,338 --> 02:04:07,450
I'm nothing, Pop.
Can't you understand that?

2111
02:04:07,536 --> 02:04:09,890
There's no spite in it anymore.

2112
02:04:09,891 --> 02:04:12,809
I'm just what I am, that's all.

2113
02:04:14,476 --> 02:04:17,840
What are you doing?
Aw, what are you doing?

2114
02:04:22,720 --> 02:04:26,001
- Why is he crying?
- Dad...

2115
02:04:27,221 --> 02:04:29,970
Will you let me go, for God's sake?

2116
02:04:30,922 --> 02:04:36,305
Will you take that phoney dream
and burn it before something happens?

2117
02:05:14,515 --> 02:05:17,433
I'll go in the morning.

2118
02:05:21,160 --> 02:05:23,490
Put him to bed.

2119
02:05:30,624 --> 02:05:34,704
Isn't that...
Isn't that remarkable?

2120
02:05:35,797 --> 02:05:38,658
Biff, he...

2121
02:05:40,298 --> 02:05:43,217
He likes me.

2122
02:05:43,496 --> 02:05:47,197
- He loves you, Willy.
- Always did, Pop.

2123
02:05:47,281 --> 02:05:49,972
Aw, Biff, he...

2124
02:05:49,973 --> 02:05:52,766
He cried. He cried to me.

2125
02:05:53,212 --> 02:05:56,872
Aw, that boy.
That boy, he's going to be magnificent.

2126
02:05:58,007 --> 02:06:00,825
Yes, outstanding,
with 20,000 behind him.

2127
02:06:00,826 --> 02:06:03,391
Come to bed, Willy.
It's all settled now.

2128
02:06:03,392 --> 02:06:06,841
Oh, yes, we'll sleep.
Come on, let's go to sleep.

2129
02:06:06,966 --> 02:06:09,574
It takes a great man
to crack thejungle.

2130
02:06:09,575 --> 02:06:12,940
I'm getting married.
Don't forget. I'm changing everything.

2131
02:06:13,024 --> 02:06:16,011
I'm gonna run that department
before the year is up.

2132
02:06:16,095 --> 02:06:18,702
Thejungle is dark
but full of diamonds.

2133
02:06:18,703 --> 02:06:22,236
Be good. You're both good boys.
Just act that way, that's all.

2134
02:06:23,751 --> 02:06:26,282
- Night, Pop.
- Night, boy.

2135
02:06:27,157 --> 02:06:30,730
- Come, dear. -S hh. One must
go in to fetch a diamond out.

2136
02:06:30,731 --> 02:06:33,466
I just want to get settled down
for a little while.

2137
02:06:33,467 --> 02:06:36,622
- I want you upstairs.
- A few minutes. I couldn't sleep now.

2138
02:06:36,748 --> 02:06:39,650
- Go. You look awful tired.
- Not like an appointment.

2139
02:06:39,734 --> 02:06:42,805
- A diamond is rough and hard to touch.
- I'll be right up.

2140
02:06:42,930 --> 02:06:45,791
- I think it's the only way.
- Sure, it's the best thing.

2141
02:06:45,875 --> 02:06:50,781
Best thing. The only way.
Everything is gonna be...

2142
02:06:50,965 --> 02:06:53,967
Aw, go on, kid. Get to bed.

2143
02:06:54,953 --> 02:06:59,454
- You look so tired. - Now, you
come right up. - Two minutes.

2144
02:07:08,076 --> 02:07:11,189
Loves me. Always loved me.
Isn't that a remarkable thing?

2145
02:07:11,273 --> 02:07:15,647
- Ben, he'll worship me for it.
- It's dark there.

2146
02:07:15,732 --> 02:07:17,539
But full of diamonds, Willy.

2147
02:07:17,540 --> 02:07:21,368
Can you imagine that magnificence
with $20,000 in his pocket?

2148
02:07:21,452 --> 02:07:23,596
Willy, come up.

2149
02:07:23,597 --> 02:07:26,373
Yes, yes, coming, coming!

2150
02:07:26,474 --> 02:07:29,460
It's very smart,
you realise, don't you, sweetheart?

2151
02:07:29,546 --> 02:07:31,353
Even Ben sees it.

2152
02:07:31,354 --> 02:07:33,895
I gotta go, baby.

2153
02:07:37,578 --> 02:07:39,783
Bye-bye.

2154
02:07:40,397 --> 02:07:43,259
When the mail comes
he'll be ahead of Bernard again.

2155
02:07:43,341 --> 02:07:47,926
- A perfect proposition all around.
- Did you see how he cried to me?

2156
02:07:47,927 --> 02:07:51,989
- Aw, I could kiss him, Ben.
- Time, William, time.

2157
02:07:52,091 --> 02:07:56,213
Ben, I always knew one way or another
we were gonna make it, Biff and I.

2158
02:07:56,297 --> 02:07:59,620
Boat! We'll be late.

2159
02:08:01,093 --> 02:08:06,393
Now, when you kick off,
I want a 70 yard boot.

2160
02:08:06,477 --> 02:08:10,052
And get right down the field
under the ball.

2161
02:08:10,136 --> 02:08:13,502
And when you hit,
hit low and hit hard,

2162
02:08:13,627 --> 02:08:16,023
because it's important, boy.

2163
02:08:16,024 --> 02:08:20,189
There's all kinds of
important people in the stands.

2164
02:08:21,072 --> 02:08:23,822
The first thing that you know...

2165
02:08:24,186 --> 02:08:25,699
Willy?

2166
02:08:25,700 --> 02:08:28,577
- Ben? Ben, where do I...?
- Willy?

2167
02:08:28,659 --> 02:08:32,689
- Ben! Ben!
- Willy!

2168
02:08:33,756 --> 02:08:35,441
Shh. Shh.

2169
02:08:35,442 --> 02:08:38,156
Shh! Shh!

2170
02:08:38,157 --> 02:08:41,173
- Willy, please come up.
- Oh.

2171
02:08:43,089 --> 02:08:45,283
- Willy!
- Shh!

2172
02:08:49,666 --> 02:08:51,697
Willy?

2173
02:08:54,189 --> 02:08:57,641
- Pop?
- Willy, answer me!

2174
02:08:57,642 --> 02:09:00,905
Willy!

2175
02:09:02,345 --> 02:09:06,209
- Willy!
- Pop! No!

2176
02:09:07,072 --> 02:09:09,720
- No!
- No!

2177
02:09:13,651 --> 02:09:17,762
It's getting dark, Linda.

2178
02:09:19,282 --> 02:09:23,517
How about it, Ma? Better get
some rest. They'll be closing the gates.

2179
02:09:23,640 --> 02:09:26,642
He had no right to do that.
There was no necessity.

2180
02:09:26,723 --> 02:09:29,601
- We would have helped him.
- Come on.

2181
02:09:29,683 --> 02:09:33,833
- Why didn't anybody come?
- It was a very nice funeral.

2182
02:09:33,834 --> 02:09:37,000
Where were the people he knew?
Maybe they blame him.

2183
02:09:37,082 --> 02:09:40,413
It's a rough world, Linda.
They wouldn't blame him.

2184
02:09:40,495 --> 02:09:45,420
I can't understand it.
First time in just about 35 years

2185
02:09:45,798 --> 02:09:49,292
we were almost free and clear.

2186
02:09:50,525 --> 02:09:53,666
He only needed a little salary.

2187
02:09:53,731 --> 02:09:56,651
He was even finished with the dentist.

2188
02:09:56,733 --> 02:09:59,694
No man only needs a little salary.

2189
02:10:01,255 --> 02:10:03,187
I can't understand it.

2190
02:10:03,188 --> 02:10:08,573
There were a lot of nice days when he'd
come home from a trip or on Sundays,

2191
02:10:08,654 --> 02:10:11,985
making the stoop,
finishing the cellar

2192
02:10:12,066 --> 02:10:16,178
when he built the extra bathroom
and put up the garage.

2193
02:10:17,575 --> 02:10:21,111
You know, Charley, I think there was
more of him in that front stoop

2194
02:10:21,193 --> 02:10:23,495
than in all the sales he ever made.

2195
02:10:23,496 --> 02:10:27,730
Yep. He was a happy man
with a bunch of cement.

2196
02:10:27,811 --> 02:10:30,607
He was wonderful with his hands.

2197
02:10:30,608 --> 02:10:33,814
He had the wrong dreams.
AII, all wrong.

2198
02:10:33,897 --> 02:10:37,110
Don't say that.
The man didn't know who he was.

2199
02:10:37,309 --> 02:10:40,145
Nobody dast blame this man.

2200
02:10:40,146 --> 02:10:42,503
You don't understand.

2201
02:10:42,899 --> 02:10:45,794
Willy was a salesman.

2202
02:10:46,353 --> 02:10:49,149
For a salesman,
there is no rock bottom to the life.

2203
02:10:49,230 --> 02:10:51,078
He don't put a bolt to a nut,

2204
02:10:51,079 --> 02:10:53,833
he don't tell you the law,
don't give you medicine.

2205
02:10:53,834 --> 02:10:56,631
He's a man way out there in the blue,

2206
02:10:57,905 --> 02:11:00,715
riding on a smile and a shoeshine.

2207
02:11:01,194 --> 02:11:05,804
When they start not smiling back,
that's an earthquake.

2208
02:11:06,002 --> 02:11:09,703
You get yourself a couple of spots
on your hat and you're finished.

2209
02:11:11,471 --> 02:11:14,487
Nobody dast blame this man.

2210
02:11:14,841 --> 02:11:18,319
A salesman has got to dream, boy.
Comes with the territory.

2211
02:11:18,500 --> 02:11:22,363
- The man didn't know who he was.
- Don't say that!

2212
02:11:22,364 --> 02:11:25,341
Why don't you come with me, Happy?

2213
02:11:25,942 --> 02:11:28,383
I'm not licked that easily.

2214
02:11:28,737 --> 02:11:31,943
I'm staying right in the city
and I'm gonna beat this racquet.

2215
02:11:33,669 --> 02:11:36,300
- Loman brothers.
- I know who I am, kid.

2216
02:11:36,301 --> 02:11:39,013
All right, boy,
I'm gonna show you and everybody

2217
02:11:39,014 --> 02:11:42,426
that Willy Loman did not die in vain.
He had a good dream.

2218
02:11:42,508 --> 02:11:45,756
It's the only dream you can have,
to come out number one man.

2219
02:11:45,839 --> 02:11:49,463
He fought it out here and this is where
I'm gonna win it for him.

2220
02:11:51,964 --> 02:11:54,651
Oh, I'll be with you in just a minute.

2221
02:11:54,965 --> 02:11:57,685
You go on, Charley.

2222
02:11:57,966 --> 02:12:00,571
Just... just a minute.

2223
02:12:04,873 --> 02:12:08,095
I never had a chance to say good-bye.

2224
02:12:17,165 --> 02:12:19,785
Help me, Willy.

2225
02:12:20,001 --> 02:12:22,442
I can't cry.

2226
02:12:23,043 --> 02:12:27,894
Seems to me you're just away on
another trip and I keep expecting you.

2227
02:12:30,319 --> 02:12:32,892
Why did you do it?

2228
02:12:34,267 --> 02:12:37,103
I search and I search,

2229
02:12:38,213 --> 02:12:41,007
and I search,

2230
02:12:42,323 --> 02:12:47,215
and I can't understand it, Willy.

2231
02:12:50,381 --> 02:12:53,932
I made the last payment
on the house today.

2232
02:12:55,437 --> 02:12:57,796
Today!

2233
02:13:04,935 --> 02:13:08,124
And there'll be nobody home.

2234
02:13:10,237 --> 02:13:13,483
We're free and clear.

2235
02:13:17,430 --> 02:13:19,905
We're free.

2236
02:13:20,679 --> 02:13:23,161
We're free.

2237
02:13:27,790 --> 02:13:30,479
We're free.

